						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Śrīraṅgadēva-mahāraya (Raṅga II) Year: Śaka 1499, <hi rend="italic">Īśvara, Kumbha</hi>, ba. 28. Sunday, <hi rend="italic">dvitiya, Hasta</hi> = 22nd February 1578 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record some grant for providing food offerings to the god, Tirumalar-uḍaiyasvāmiyār at Dēvakkāpuram, a <hi rend="italic">dēvasthāna</hi> in Murugamaṅgalappaṟṟu, adjacent to Rājagambiraṉ-malai in Mēlkuṉṟa-nāḍu in Palkuṉṟa-kōṭṭam (a sub-division) of Jayaṅgoṇḍachōḻa-maṇḍalam, on the auspicious occasions in the months of <hi rend="italic">Māsi</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Vaikāsi</hi>, for the merit of Agastiyappa-nāyakkar of Vēlūr. Other details are not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
